IX. 1 In the same way, it is not the business of generals to give up men, conquesta, landa, obtained in war. By this rulo, Syria was talren from Tigranes, though Lucullus had gisen it to him. of Sophonisba, who had been taken prisoner in war, Scipio says that the judgment and decision oi the Senate and Psople oi Rome was to determin03 and that therefore Masinissa, though the general by whom she was taken, could not give her liberty. That orer other things which are taken as prize oi war, a certain disposal is concedcd to persons in authority, we have seen; not so much from the force oi their power, as from the customs oi each people: on thch subject we hare already spoken sufficiently.
